body_html:
As a temporary workaround, can you try the following to see if it fixes the issue?

python quantize_graph.py --input ~/proc/frozen_inference_optimized.pb --output ~/proc/frozen_inference_optimized_quantized.pb --output_node_names on_logits,preprocess/centered_bgr --mode eightbit

Here I've added the input node to the list of outputs. The issue is that it's deciding that the input node 'preprocess/centered_bgr' isn't needed, so I'm forcing it to include it by listing it as an output. If that fixes the immediate issue, it will give more information about what's going wrong.
